The US amends the rules for obtaining a visa
People must introduce themselves to the visa application services before they talk to the consulate; costs will be reduced in this way.
From 10 January 2011, the procedures for applying for a visa in the Embassy of the United States and in the Consulates will change.
In the new procedure, most applicants must present themselves to the visa application services (ASC, the initial letters in English) prior to their consultation in the consulate.
The staff of the ASC shall record the applicant's biometric data, which shall be reviewed by the consulate prior to the discussion.
The new procedure has certain advantages for the aspirators, including:
The total cost of processing the visa is reduced, since it is no longer necessary to pay separately the appointment date, the processing of the visa application and the transport service with which the document is handed out.
The applicant shall provide only one payment covering the three services.
The current price remains unchanged: the counterpart to 140 dollars for a tourist visa, 150 dollars for visas with application (including temporary visas) and 390 dollars for hands and investors.
Those who only want to extend their visas do not need to have a conversation in the consulate, they only have to imagine themselves at the next ASC, where they present their documents and their fingerprints are taken.
As the biometric data is collected in the ASC, applicants who need a second date for the consultation in the consulate remain there less time than before.
Those who apply for the visa in the consulates of Ciudad Juice, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo no longer have to pay the service charge of 26 dollars.
Additional information on the new visa application procedure can be found on the following website: http://mexico.usembasi.gov/boletines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
